column1: # The 1830 bracketed total figure has been omitted. There are no associated monthly readings, which don't start until 1831, so it seems likely to be an estimate.
# The bracketed figure for July 1879 (and the 1879 total) has been retained but is suspect.
# Bracketed July-December 1891 figures omitted. The gauge was defective; the values were computed.
# Site seems likely to be Bootham School (20 Bootham) or the Headmaster's House (49 Bootham).
# Observers John Ford and Fielden Thorp were both headmasters of Bootham School.
